 class=\"sig-paren\">(</span><em class=\"sig-param\"><span class=\"n\"><span class=\"pre\">dim</span></span><span class=\"o\"><span class=\"pre\">=</span></span><span class=\"default_value\"><span class=\"pre\">None</span></span></em>, <em class=\"sig-param\"><span class=\"n\"><span class=\"pre\">keepdim</span></span><span class=\"o\"><span class=\"pre\">=</span></span><span class=\"default_value\"><span class=\"pre\">False</span></span></em>, <em class=\"sig-param\"><span class=\"o\"><span class=\"pre\">*</span></span></em>, <em class=\"sig-param\"><span class=\"n\"><span class=\"pre\">dtype</span></span><span class=\"o\"><span class=\"pre\">=</span></span><span class=\"default_value\"><span class=\"pre\">None</span></span></em><span class=\"sig-paren\">)</span> <span class=\"sig-return\"><span class=\"sig-return-icon\">→</span> <span class=\"sig-return-typehint\"><a class=\"reference internal\" href=\"../mindspore.Tensor.html#mindspore.Tensor\" title=\"mindspore.Tensor\"><span class=\"pre\">Tensor</span></a></span></span><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"https://atomgit.com/mindspore/mindspore/blob/v2.8.0/mindspore/ops/api_def/method_doc/sum_doc.yaml\"><span class=\"viewcode-link\"><span class=\"pre\">[source]</span></span></a><a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#mindspore.Tensor.sum\" title=\"Permalink to this definition\"></a></dt>\n<dd><p>Calculate sum of Tensor elements over a given dim.</p>\n<div class=\"admonition note\">\n<p class=\"admonition-title\">Note</p>\n<p>The <cite>dim</cite> with tensor type is only used for compatibility with older versions and is not recommended.</p>\n</div>\n<dl class=\"field-list simple\">\n<dt class=\"field-odd\">Parameters</dt>\n<dd class=\"field-odd\"><ul class=\"simple\">\n<li><p><strong>dim</strong> (<em>Union</em><em>[</em><em>None</em><em>, </em><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"https://docs.python.org/3/library/functions.html#int\" title=\"(in Python v3.13)\"><em>int</em></a><em>, </em><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#tuple\" title=\"(in Python v3.13)\"><em>tuple</em></a><em>(</em><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"https://docs.python.org/3/library/functions.html#int\" title=\"(in Python v3.13)\"><em>int</em></a><em>)</em><em>, </em><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#list\" title=\"(in Python v3.13)\"><em>list</em></a><em>(</em><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"https://docs.python.org/3/library/functions.html#int\" title=\"(in Python v3.13)\"><em>int</em></a><em>)</em><em>, </em><a class=\"reference internal\" href=\"../mindspore.Tensor.html#mindspore.Tensor\" title=\"mindspore.Tensor\"><em>Tensor</em></a><em>]</em><em>, </em><em>optional</em>) – Dimensions along which a sum is performed.\nIf <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">None</span></code> , sum all the elements of the self tensor.\nIf the <cite>dim</cite> is a tuple or list of ints, a sum is performed on all the dimensions specified in the tuple.\nMust be in the range <span class=\"math notranslate nohighlight\">\\([-self.ndim, self.ndim)\\)</span> . Default: <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">None</span></code> .</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>keepdim</strong> (<a class=\"reference external\" href=\"https://docs.python.org/3/library/functions.html#bool\" title=\"(in Python v3.13)\"><em>bool</em></a><em>, </em><em>optional</em>) – Whether the output tensor has <cite>dim</cite> retained or not.\nIf <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">True</span></code> , keep these reduced dimensions and the length is 1.\nIf <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">False</span></code> , don't keep these dimensions. Default: <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">False</span></code> .</p></li>\n</ul>\n</dd>\n<dt class=\"field-even\">Keyword Arguments</dt>\n<dd class=\"field-even\"><p><strong>dtype</strong> (<a class=\"reference internal\" href=\"../mindspore.dtype.html#mindspore.dtype\" title=\"mindspore.dtype\"><code class=\"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">mindspore.dtype</span></code></a>, optional) – The desired data type of returned Tensor. Default: <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">None</span></code> .</p>\n</dd>\n<dt class=\"field-odd\">Returns</dt>\n<dd class=\"field-odd\"><p>A Tensor, sum of elements over a given <cite>dim</cite> in <cite>self</cite>.</p>\n</dd>\n<dt class=\"field-even\">Raises</dt>\n<dd class=\"field-even\"><ul class=\"simple\">\n<li><p><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"https://docs.python.org/3/library/exceptions.html#TypeError\" title=\"(in Python v3.13)\"><strong>TypeError</strong></a> – If <cite>dim</cite> is not an int, tulpe(int), list(int), Tensor or None.</p></li>\n<li><p><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"https://docs.python.org/3/library/exceptions.html#ValueError\" title=\"(in Python v3.13)\"><strong>ValueError</strong></a> – If <cite>dim</cite> is not in the range <span class=\"math notranslate nohighlight\">\\([-self.ndim, self.ndim)\\)</span> .</p></li>\n<li><p><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"https://docs.python.org/3/library/exceptions.html#TypeError\" title=\"(in Python v3.13)\"><strong>TypeError</strong></a> – If <cite>keepdim</cite> is not a bool.</p></li>\n</ul>\n</dd>\n</dl>\n<dl class=\"simple\">\n<dt>Supported Platforms:</dt><dd><p><code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">Ascend</span></code> <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">GPU</span></code> <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">CPU</span></code></p>\n</dd>\n</dl>\n<p class=\"rubric\">Examples</p>\n<div class=\"doctest highlight-default notranslate\"><div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"gp\">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><spa